  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      To examine effects of intensive lipid lowering therapy with atorvastatin on stabilization of
      coronary plaque by using optical coherence tomography (OCT) in patients with acute coronary
      syndrome.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Patients with acute coronary syndrome (myocardial infarction or unstable angina) who will
      undergo PCI and have at least one atherosclerotic lesion of &gt;25% stenosis other than culprit
      lesions of current ACS are enrolled. Fibrous cap thickness of a target coronary plaque is
      evaluated by optical coherence tomography.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
